# Repository: AI Guardrails for Engineering Projects

## Purpose

This repository provides AI coding assistant configurations and guardrails for
software engineering projects. It contains tool-specific instructions (Cursor, Claude,
GitHub Copilot, etc.) derived from a canonical set of engineering standards.

## Key Characteristics

- **Governance-first approach**: Documentation as executable instructions
- **Defense-in-depth security**: Never commit secrets (3-layer protection)
- **Quality gates**: Pre-commit hooks, CI/CD enforcement
- **Tool-native configs**: Optimized for each AI assistant
- **Single source of truth**: All configs derived from CONTEXT.md

## Usage

Include this repository in your projects:

```bash
# As a git submodule
git submodule add <repo-url> .ai-guardrails

# Or copy files directly
cp -r .ai-guardrails/.cursor .
cp -r .ai-guardrails/CLAUDE.md .
cp -r .ai-guardrails/CONTRIBUTING.md .
```

## Supported AI Tools

- ✅ Cursor (via .cursor/rules/*.mdc)
- ✅ Claude Desktop (via CLAUDE.md)
- ✅ Claude Projects (via .claudeprompt)
- ✅ GitHub Copilot (via .github/copilot-instructions.md)
- ✅ Aider (via .aider/.aider.conf.yml)
- ✅ Continue.dev (via .vscode/settings.json)
